* She noticed him, finally!
D hadn't known if she would have just brushed him away but she didn't and he 
kept on tugging.
But D let go of Fenox when she walked towards and room and entered, looking 
behind his massive shoulder towards Vlad and growling before entering too.
D did a little hop, skip and a jump as he passed from hall to room to make 
sure that his tail wouldn't ne cought in the door when it closed behind him. 
He'd learned that the hard way.
He looked Fenox in the face before looking back at the door as it closed, 
Vlad left in the hall with that dog thing he was with.*

" Not good."

* D said, turning his head back towards Fenox.*

" Smell wrong."

* He hoped that she could understand that he was trying to say that Vlad was 
bad. His voice gruff when he said it to try and get the pout across.*
